a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Mangools is best suited for beginners, bloggers, freelancers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. RankMath, meanwhile, shines for WordPress users, bloggers, small business sites, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2014, Mangools describes itself as \"Simple and affordable SEO toolset with excellent keyword research.\" RankMath, established in 2018, positions itself as \"Advanced WordPress SEO plugin with AI-powered content optimization.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **RankMath** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (6 vs 5), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Mangools is a poor choice — far from it. Mangools excels in its own right, particularly for beginners and bloggers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value generous free version with advanced features, go with RankMath. If beautiful and intuitive kwfinder tool matters more to you, Mangools is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
